# Working rules (whole engagement)

1. For each task, create a feature branch off `main` named `fix/<short-description>`. Never commit directly to main.
2. Before any code change, post a 2–4 sentence plan describing what you'll edit and why.
3. After each non-trivial change, run `npm run lint` and `npx tsc --noEmit` for fast feedback; fix any failure before continuing. Run the full `npm run build` once before opening the PR (not after every change — it's slow).
4. If a task touches `supabase/migrations`, after creating the migration tell me the exact `supabase db push` (or equivalent) command to run, and wait for me to confirm before assuming the schema changed. Then run `npm run types:db` to regenerate types.
5. When a task is done, commit with a clear message (`fix(redeem): require active subscription`), then summarize: what changed, what files, what I should test manually.
6. Never run `git push`, never run anything that costs money (Stripe live mode, Resend bulk sends), and never install a new npm dependency on your own. If a task needs a new package, STOP, tell me which package and why, and give me the install command to run myself.
7. If a fix is bigger than expected, stop and tell me — don't expand scope silently.

